# Demonstrates: C97 — dead guards provably false from field constraints

# This file covers both a bounded interval contradiction and a positive-constraint contradiction.

precept DeadGuardsDemo

field Score as number default 50 min 0 max 100
field Rate as number default 5 positive

state Review initial
state Approved
state Escalated

event Submit
event Escalate

# C97: Score can never exceed 150 when the field is capped at 100.
# EXPECT: C97 | severity=warning | match=exact | message=Guard 'when Score > 150' is provably always false — this row can never execute. | line=19 | start=27 | end=38
from Review on Submit when Score > 150 -> transition Approved
from Review on Submit -> transition Approved

# C97: a positive field can never satisfy <= 0.
# EXPECT: C97 | severity=warning | match=exact | message=Guard 'when Rate <= 0' is provably always false — this row can never execute. | line=24 | start=29 | end=38
from Review on Escalate when Rate <= 0 -> transition Escalated
from Review on Escalate -> transition Escalated
